Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.4.2) using npm
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json with the new dependency

### 2. Analytics Component Integration
- Modified `app/layout.tsx` to include Vercel Analytics
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body tag in RootLayout

### 3. Implementation Details
Following the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects:
- The Analytics component is placed inside the body tag, after the children
- This ensures analytics tracking is enabled across all pages in the application
- The implementation uses the Next.js-specific package (`@vercel/analytics/next`)

### 4. Verification
- Build completed successfully with no errors
- TypeScript compilation passed
- All routes generated correctly (/, /_not-found, /docs)
- No breaking changes introduced to existing functionality

## Files Modified
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies

## Next Steps
After deployment to Vercel, analytics will automatically start tracking:
1. Page views
2. User interactions
3. Performance metrics

Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section.
